node.text: The Chicago Cubs Hall of Fame: Baseball legends. Former players and managers. Beloved broadcasters and announcers. Team owners and front office executives. The following individuals have been inducted into our Hall of Fame for their dedication to Cubs baseball, both on and off the field. Forever immortalized in our historic ballpark, the Chicago Cubs Hall of Fame is located in the Left Field Budweiser Bleacher concourse and includes 56 plaques which represent individuals previously enshrined in the original Cubs Hall of Fame (1982-86), those enshrined in the Cubs Walk of Fame (1992-98), Cubs in the National Baseball Hall of Fame and a new 2021 inductee, Margaret Donahue, who broke gender barriers as Major League Baseball’s first female officer who was not a team owner. Visit Cubs.com/HallofFame to see all inductees. Who should be inducted into the Cubs HOF next?
